Numerical Integration with the Midpoint Rule
Project Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of the Midpoint Rule, a numerical integration method used to approximate the value of a definite integral. The method divides the integration interval into several equal subintervals and evaluates the function at the midpoint of each subinterval to estimate the area under the curve.
The calculation process includes determining midpoint values, evaluating the function at each midpoint, summing the resulting function values, and calculating the final approximation of the definite integral. The Midpoint Rule is widely used in numerical analysis due to its simplicity and relatively good accuracy.

